OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJacob Rees-Mogg empty desk 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fnote to civil servants     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Finsulting, says union      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Cabinet minister Jacob Rees-Mogg has   
OL,6, been criticised for leaving a note for 
OL,7, civil servants, saying "sorry you were 
OL,8, out when I visited".                   
OL,10,FThe note, printed on government paper  
OL,11,Fwith Mr Rees-Mogg's title, was left at 
OL,12,Fempty desks and read "I look forward to
OL,13,Fseeing you in the office very soon."   
OL,15,FMr Rees-Mogg has said all civil        
OL,16,Fservants must stop working from home.  
OL,18,FFDA union boss Dave Penman said the    
OL,19,Fnote was crass and insulting, and      
OL,20,Fundermined civil service leadership.   
